00:00:01.930 --> 00:00:04.900
Hello Here is the recipe for Linz pie (from Austria)

00:00:05.900 --> 00:00:13.300
ingredients : 250g flour, 100g almond powder, 125g butter, 100g sugar, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon,300g rapsberry jam, 1 egg yolk, 1 teaspoon milk, a pinch of salt

00:00:14.399 --> 00:00:16.720
Put the flour in a bowl

00:00:16.720 --> 00:00:20.970
add almond powder

00:00:20.970 --> 00:00:23.449
sugar and salt

00:00:23.449 --> 00:00:24.730
cinnamon

00:00:24.730 --> 00:00:31.659
mix with a spoon

00:00:31.659 --> 00:00:38.600
add butter

00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:45.730
mix with hand

00:00:53.920 --> 00:00:55.480
add eggs

00:00:55.480 --> 00:01:00.970
it will take some time to form a ball

00:01:17.840 --> 00:01:22.120
Once your ball formed, put in clingfilm

00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:29.120
place in the fridge for at least 2 hours

00:01:33.610 --> 00:01:36.570
roll out the dough directly on a parchment paper at the size of the mold

00:01:36.570 --> 00:01:40.170
the dough is friable, it will be easier to move it in the mold

00:01:45.610 --> 00:01:49.050
add flour

00:01:51.810 --> 00:01:53.740
Keep unused dough

00:01:53.740 --> 00:01:56.550
for cake decoration

00:01:56.550 --> 00:01:59.520
place the dough on the mould

00:02:15.369 --> 00:02:18.209
cut edges

00:02:23.359 --> 00:02:37.700
raise the edges and prick the dough

00:02:44.879 --> 00:02:51.879
spread the jam

00:02:56.200 --> 00:03:01.500
cut strips of unused dough to decorate the cake

00:03:05.119 --> 00:03:06.669
place them

00:03:10.249 --> 00:03:12.700
Add a teaspoon of milk to your egg yolk

00:03:16.549 --> 00:03:34.500
spread on the dough. Bake at 200°C (400F) for 25 minutes and at 180°C (350F) for 10 minutes

00:03:36.229 --> 00:03:41.179
eat it cold and "bon appétit"

00:03:41.179 --> 00:03:43.200
stay tuned for next recipe !

